    "abstract": "This work adopts the detection method of Quantum Support Vector Machine (QSVM) to improve the accuracy of credit card fraud detection. Quantum-SMOTE is utilized to address the issue of imbalanced credit card datasets. The QSVM model maps classical data to a high-dimensional Hilbert space through quantum feature mapping, thereby enhancing the separability of features.",
    "domain": "Tabular",
    "key_claims": [
      "QSVM with Quantum-SMOTE achieves 98.8% accuracy and AUC=0.992 on the Kaggle credit card fraud dataset",
      "Quantum-SMOTE outperforms classical undersampling by 6.4 percentage points in accuracy (98.8% vs 92.4%)",
      "QSVM performance gap over classical SVM widens with qubit count: 0.8pp at 4-qubit, 2.4pp at 8-qubit, 3.7pp at 10-qubit",
      "Quantum-SMOTE uses quantum swap tests and quantum rotation to generate minority class samples without KNN interpolation",
      "ZZFeatureMap-based quantum kernel (inner product in Hilbert space of dimension 2^n) is the core of QSVM classification"
    ],
    "parsed_at": "2026-05-14T00:00:00Z",
    "arxivist_version": "1.0"
  },

